  funFact: The album title and the iconic mask on the cover are a tribute to Elvis
    Presley. "Hellvisback" plays on the phrase "Elvis is back", blending it with
    "Hell" to create a darker, more rebellious alter ego. It marks a crucial point
    in Italian rap history, fusing heavy rock, live drums, and dark electronic synths
    with raw hardcore rap lyrics.
